    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera is powered by the 3.6L M96/03 flat-six, utilizing VarioCam Plus for an optimized torque curve and 320 hp. The power is managed via a G96/01 6-speed manual transaxle, offering short, tactile throws and precise gear synchronization. The chassis retains its signature rear-engine weight bias, providing exceptional mechanical grip and communicative steering through the hydraulic rack-and-pinion system. Maintenance is up to date, including a proactive IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal (RMS) to ensure long-term reliability. While the exterior shows the honest patina of a dedicated driver, the suspension bushings are tight, and the throttle response is instantaneous. This is a mechanically robust example for those who prioritize the analog driving dynamics of the late-90s/early-00s Zuffenhausen era.",
